raw_data.title: IT Business Systems Analyst - Intermediate
raw_data.description: Build and support new IT systems and applications for complex data sets.  Work through and analyze large complex data sets.  Connect and support data sources that flow into data warehouses using various APIs.  Connect and support data warehouses that pass data into business analytics tools such as PowerBI and Tableau through an AWS server or equivalent. Support and navigate off-the-shelf ETL solutions.

raw_data.title: IT Business Systems Specialist
raw_data.description: Designing and maintaining IT data systems and databases utilizing R and Python tools; this includes fixing coding errors and other data-related problems.  Mining data from primary and secondary sources, then reorganizing said data in a format utilizing data visualization software such as Tableau, DOMO, or Looker that can be easily read. Using statistical tools to interpret data sets, paying attention to trends and patterns that could be valuable for diagnostic and predictive analytics efforts.  Collaborating with programmers, engineers, and organizational leaders to identify opportunities for process improvements, recommend system modifications, and develop policies for data governance. Creating appropriate documentation that allows stakeholders to understand the steps of the data analysis process and duplicate or replicate the analysis if necessary.

raw_data.title: IT Consultant
raw_data.description: Architect the vision for insightful storytelling (excellent information/presentation design) by using DOMO, Tableau, Power BI and Looker tools.  Works with IT partners to develop and analyze business intelligence needs.  Ensure IT data quality and ongoing evolution.  Recommend strategies leveraging analytics tools on an analytical approach to closing the loop on implementation/optimization efforts to ensure meaningful impact/action/goal achievement.  Assesses current or planned future IT environment & third-party integrations.

raw_data.title: IT Data Analyst/ Programmer - Intermediate
raw_data.description: Deliver strong Python and SQL development and maintenance techniques surrounding data movement to include technologies.  Strong background in UNIX and Bash administration.  Familiarity with AWS and other cloud hosting solutions a plus.  Investigate and understand different data sources and the ability to connect to a wide variety of 3rd party APIs. Assist in architecting, mapping, developing, and testing data movement to data warehouses (Redshift and others), with emphasis on the Extract-Transform-Load (ETL) process.  Development of ETL source and target mapping design/specifications based on the business requirements and ETL standards and architecture.  Assist in driving roadmap and execution of critical client engagements by collaborating with your lead, internal team, and clients.  Develop, document, and execute SQL/stored procedures/server scripts as needed to support ETL code.  Determine ETL hardware/software requirements and assist with production setup & migrations.

raw_data.title: IT Web Manager
raw_data.description: Responsible for IT web marketing structure, processes, and methodologies, specifically related to search engine optimization and paid media.  Responsible for supporting IT web teams and clients in the following areas: •Content development, including copywriting, editing, and proofreading •Website and landing page updates •Audits, including content, technical, social, competitor, paid media, etc. •Collaborates with web design, development, and content staff to monitor and improve search engine optimization (SEO) results for the company’s site(s) •Create and monitor targeted A/B tests to increase conversions and optimize the website •Monitoring site traffic and activities related to client acquisition and retention
